The file is being read twice for JSON files - once in the YAML branch check (implicitly) and once in the JSON.parse call. Consider reading the file content once into a variable before the conditional check to avoid redundant I/O operations.
```suggestion
    const content = fs.readFileSync(file, 'utf8');
    if (file.endsWith('.yaml') || file.endsWith('.yml')) {
      return yaml.parse(content);
    }

    // attempt JSON by default
    return JSON.parse(content);
```
